root_MSE={}
MAPE = {}
for m in range(1,p):
    regressor = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators = m, random_state = 0,oob_score = True)
    regressor.fit(X_train_values, y_train_values)

    # Out-of_sample MSE
    test_pred =regressor.predict(X_test)
    root_MSE[m] = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, test_pred))
    MAPE[m] = metrics.mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test, test_pred)

p = len(df_train.columns)
root_MSE2_insample ={}
root_MSE2={}
MAPE2 ={}
MAPE2_insample = {}
for m in range(1,p):
    regressor = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators = m, random_state = 0,oob_score = True)
    regressor.fit(transformer.transform(X_train), y_train_values)

    # In-sample and Out-of_sample RMSE and MAPE
    train_pred =regressor.predict(transformer.transform(X_train))
    test_pred =regressor.predict(transformer.transform(X_test))

    root_MSE2_insample[m] = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_train, train_pred))
    root_MSE2[m] = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, test_pred))

    MAPE2_insample[m] =metrics.mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_train, train_pred)
    MAPE2[m] = metrics.mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test, test_pred)

    # In-sample and Out-of_sample RMSE and MAPE

    GB_MAPE_outsample[m] = metrics.mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test, test_pred)
